column5: I changed the oil in my ATV, greased all the fittings, & fabricated a bracket to hold the spare tire for my trailer.  Woohoo!  Today I'm going Christmas shopping! Not nearly as exciting as the crane operator.
Don't worry I wasn't the patient I was the baby sitter
Had a boring day ice fishing for jumbos
Same thing I do everyday
Same thing I do everyday
You've made big news man, Ive been hearing all about your helicopter rescue... and have seen a bunch of pictures on the web... including this one http://imgur.com/gallery/apiAmOM
That helicopter crew did an outstanding job and it's good to know guys like that are around when and if we need them.
This was such and interesting story it even made our 11pm news cast. Awesome rescue
You made it on several news papers too
I wonder how much the rescuee was billed to cover the rescue?
Are you guys not reading the 2nd post? Kickingfrog was not the guy out there on the crane being rescued..... Lol

No big deal just went to work on a construction crane and then had a massive explosion and fire underneath me. I climbed out the end of the boom and waited for an hour while the flames went higher and then I was rescued by a helicopter.
Not me. I just picked up a sick 20 month old early from daycare.
I did paint preparation wahoo !
Good to hear he was rescued Rob, that's a bad spot to be trapped.  Is there a link to the story anywhere ??
I would think at this point most of the major tv news would have it.
Anybody have tips on cleaning puke off of a kids car seat?
Ask the wife. NO MY JOB MAN.
Drive it to Kingston and throw it in....
ITS BEEN MY JOB MAN!   LOL
On a brighter note he probably didn't get cold out in the elements

Went to Hoffmans in Stayner this morning, loaded up on on smoked ham, beef rouladen, pepperettes and a bunch of other goodies.  Came home, off to the garage, mixed a litre of gas for the old auger,  3 primes, 2nd pull and it awoke from its off season slumber.  Not bad for a 20+ year old Jiffy.
Nice !!!!Amazing rescue by the SAR techs at CFB Trenton !!! Almost as good as firing up a 20 year old jiffy LOL.
Ya that rescue was amazing I just seen it on the news !!!! Kudos to our military boys for getting him off that crane safe & sound !!!! Amazing for sure !!!!
Ya, that puts another twist on Chets nuts roasting over an open fire.  Lucky to be alive.
http://www.theepochtimes.com/n3/404002-kingston-fire-big-fire-burning-in-downtown-in-ontario-city/
Many many many years ago I used to live not far from there,reminds me of the train wreck in Mississauga 35 or so years ago when I had 10 extra people living in my house for a week..   vance
Well, if they took him to the hospital to make sure he was OK they should have stopped by his house so he'd have clean underwear!!
I sat in a hospital psych ward for 9 hours
Epic dude. All I did was go fishing, and spend an approximate 6 hours in traffic, going to and from Barrie.

After I retired I worked Part time for Enterprise Car rentals shuttling cars around the GTA and I made more money going to Barrie in the winter than you can believe.One day we made 5 round trips from Markham going up the 400 unbelievable!!! People who had been in a big accident where impatiently wait for rentals,one guy gave me a hard time for not getting there sooner,I told him unlike his this car was in one piece,and he did complain to the office and I was chastised  vance
I sat in a hospital psych ward for 9 hours You make it too easy...
If you were a friend of mine I would ask if you were a patient,but your not BUT BUT BUT okay I wont ask!!!!   vance
I spent my day wondering what i could put off until tomorrow.. it worked....
..so the same thing as yesterday TJ...
